## 1. Your model relationships are everything!

Well not everything, but you get my gist. If your model realtionships are set up correctly ActiveRecord makes your life smooth as butter. I discovered this 14 hours of work into my project when I was staring at this line of Active Record Query that I managed to smash together on my keyboard.

```
<% MemoryDeck.joins(:user).where("user_id = ?", params[:user_id]).group("title").each  do |deck| %>
            <li><%= link_to deck.title, memory_deck_path(deck)  %></li>
          <% end %>
```

I want to take a minute and aknowledge how beautiful that line is. Bound paramaters, joins, group by what?! On a side note: If anybody has any questions about this feel free to reach out to me via linkedin. https://www.linkedin.com/in/nico-roulston-47852548/ .
I hit a snag of epic proportions while writing the above and realized this was way harder than it should be.
